<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja seaduse &uuml;lesanne </eesti>
<inglise>Purpose of Working and Rest Time Act </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja seadus s&auml;testab t&ouml;&ouml;tajate t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja kestuse ning korralduse alused. </eesti>
<inglise>The Working and Rest Time Act provides the duration and bases for the organisation of working time and rest time of employees. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja seaduse rakendusala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Working and Rest Time Act </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja seadus laieneb k&otilde;igile t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu alusel t&ouml;&ouml;tavatele isikutele, v&auml;lja arvatud erandjuhud, mil t&ouml;&ouml;tajate puhkeaega reguleeritakse muude seaduste v&otilde;i Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rustega. </eesti>
<inglise>The Working and Rest Time Act extends to all persons employed under an employment contract except in exceptional cases where the rest time of employees is regulated by other Acts or regulations of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aja m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of working time </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aeg on seaduse, haldusakti, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu v&otilde;i poolte kokkuleppega m&auml;&auml;ratud aeg, mille kestel t&ouml;&ouml;taja on kohustatud t&auml;itma oma t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesandeid, alludes t&ouml;&ouml;andja juhtimisele ja kontrollile. </eesti>
<inglise>Working time is time determined by law, administrative legislation, a collective agreement, employment contract or agreement of the parties during which employees are required to perform their duties in subordination to the management and supervision of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;ajanormi m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of standard for working time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;ajanorm on seaduse, haldusakti, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga m&auml;&auml;ratud t&ouml;&ouml;tundide arv mingis kalendriajavahemikus (p&auml;ev, n&auml;dal, kuu v&otilde;i muu ajavahemik). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The standard for working time is the number of working hours determined by law, administrative legislation, a collective agreement or employment contract for a certain period of calendar time (day, week, month or other period of time). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riiklik t&ouml;&ouml;ajanorm m&auml;&auml;ratakse seaduse v&otilde;i seaduse t&auml;itmiseks antud haldusaktiga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The national standard for working time is determined by an Act or administrative legislation passed for implementation of the Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga m&auml;&auml;ratud t&ouml;&ouml;ajanorm ei v&otilde;i &uuml;letada riigi poolt kehtestatud t&ouml;&ouml;ajanormi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The standard for working time determined by a collective agreement or employment contract shall not exceed the standard for working time established by the state. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva, -vahetuse ja -n&auml;dala m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definitions of working day, working shift and working week </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;ev on ajavahemik &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evas, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja on kohustatud t&auml;itma oma t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesandeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A working day is the period of time during a twenty-four hour period when employees are required to perform their duties. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;vahetus on ajavahemik, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja on kohustatud t&auml;itma oma t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesandeid vahetustega t&ouml;&ouml;l. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A working shift is the period of time when employees are required to perform their duties in shifts at work. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;vahetus v&otilde;ib alata &uuml;hel ja l&otilde;ppeda teisel &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>A working shift may begin during one twenty-four hour period and end during the next twenty-four hour period. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;n&auml;dal on ajavahemik n&auml;dalas, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja on kohustatud t&auml;itma oma t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesandeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A working week is the period of time during a week when employees are required to perform their duties. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja rakendab kahe puhkep&auml;evaga viiep&auml;evast t&ouml;&ouml;n&auml;dalat, mis algab esmasp&auml;evast v&otilde;i muust n&auml;dalap&auml;evast, olenevalt t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures kehtestatud t&ouml;&ouml;ajare&zcaron;iimist. </eesti>
<inglise>Employers shall implement a five-day working week with two days off, which begins on Monday or another weekday depending on the working time regime established by the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkeaja m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of rest time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Puhkeaeg on aeg, mille kestel t&ouml;&ouml;taja on vaba t&ouml;&ouml;kohustuste t&auml;itmisest ja v&otilde;ib seda kasutada oma &auml;ran&auml;gemise j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Rest time is the time during which employees are released from performing their duties and which they may use at their discretion. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Puhkeaeg on t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evasisene, t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evadevaheline ja igan&auml;dalane. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Rest time is prescribed during working days, between working days and every week. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkeaja hulka kuuluvad riigip&uuml;had ja puhkused. </eesti>
<inglise>Public holidays and holidays are included in rest time. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aja l&uuml;hendamine ja puhkeaja pikendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Reduction of working time and extension of rest time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tajale seaduse v&otilde;i haldusaktiga kehtestatud t&ouml;&ouml;aega v&otilde;ib l&uuml;hendada ja puhkeaega pikendada kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Working time established for employees by law or administrative legislation may be reduced and rest time may be extended by a collective agreement or employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;tajale seaduse v&otilde;i haldusaktiga kehtestatud t&ouml;&ouml;aega v&otilde;ib l&uuml;hendada ning puhkeaega pikendada t&ouml;&ouml;andja &uuml;hepoolse otsusega, kui sellega ei kaasne palgatingimuste halvenemine. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Working time established for employees by law or administrative legislation may be reduced and rest time may be extended by a unilateral decision of the employer unless this results in a deterioration of wage conditions. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Lapsi kasvatavate isikute soodustused </eesti>
<inglise>Benefits for persons raising children </inglise>
<eesti>Soodustused, mis on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 14, 18, 19 ja 30 ette n&auml;htud naisele, kes kasvatab lapsinvaliidi v&otilde;i alla 14-aastast last, laienevad ka: </eesti>
<inglise>The benefits prescribed in &sect;&sect; 14, 18, 19 and 30 of this Act for a woman raising a disabled child or child under fourteen years of age also extend to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) isikule, kes kasvatab ilma emata lapsinvaliidi v&otilde;i alla 14-aastast last; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a person raising a motherless disabled child or child under fourteen years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>2) alla 14-aastase lapse eestkostjale; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a guardian of a child under fourteen years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>3) lapsinvaliidi eestkostjale v&otilde;i hooldajale. </eesti>
<inglise>3) a guardian or curator of a disabled child. </inglise>
<eesti>II peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter II </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aja kestus </eesti>
<inglise>Duration of Working Time </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aja &uuml;ldine riiklik norm </eesti>
<inglise>General national standard for working time </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;aja &uuml;ldine riiklik norm ei v&otilde;i &uuml;letada kaheksat tundi p&auml;evas ja 40 tundi n&auml;dalas. </eesti>
<inglise>The general national standard for the working time of employees shall not exceed eight hours per day and forty hours per week. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>L&uuml;hendatud t&ouml;&ouml;aeg </eesti>
<inglise>Reduced working time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) L&uuml;hendatud t&ouml;&ouml;aeg ei v&otilde;i &uuml;letada: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Reduced working time shall not exceed: </inglise>
<eesti>1) 13-14-aastastel t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel 20 tundi n&auml;dalas; </eesti>
<inglise>1) 20 hours per week for employees who are 13-14 years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>2) 15-16-aastastel t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel 25 tundi n&auml;dalas; </eesti>
<inglise>2) 25 hours per week for employees who are 15-16 years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>3) 17-aastastel t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel 30 tundi n&auml;dalas. </eesti>
<inglise>3) 30 hours per week for employees who are 17 years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;tajatel, kes t&ouml;&ouml;tavad allmaat&ouml;&ouml;del, tervistkahjustavatel ja eriiseloomuga t&ouml;&ouml;del, on l&uuml;hendatud t&ouml;&ouml;aja kestus kuni 35 tundi n&auml;dalas. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The duration of reduced working time for employees who perform underground work, work that poses a health hazard or work of a special nature is up to thirty-five hours per week. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Koolide ja muude lasteasutuste &otilde;petajatel, kasvatajatel ja teistel pedagoogikaspetsialistidel on l&uuml;hendatud t&ouml;&ouml;aja kestus kuni 35 tundi n&auml;dalas. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The duration of shortened working time for teachers, educators and other pedagogical specialists in schools and other child care institutions is up to thirty-five hours per week. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tervistkahjustavate t&ouml;&ouml;de n&auml;idustuste, allmaat&ouml;&ouml;de ja eriiseloomuga t&ouml;&ouml;de loetelu, kus t&ouml;&ouml;tamisel rakendatakse l&uuml;hendatud t&ouml;&ouml;aega, ning l&uuml;hendatud t&ouml;&ouml;aja kestuse kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Government of the Republic shall establish a list of indicators of work which poses a health hazard, is underground work or work of a special nature where reduced working time is applicable, and the duration of the reduced working time. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Ametikohtade loetelu, kus t&ouml;&ouml;tamisel rakendatakse &otilde;petajatele, kasvatajatele ja teistele pedagoogika spetsialistidele l&uuml;hendatud t&ouml;&ouml;aega, ning l&uuml;hendatud t&ouml;&ouml;aja kestuse kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Government of the Republic shall establish a list of positions where reduced working time is applicable with respect to teachers, educators and other pedagogical specialists, and the duration of the reduced working time. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kollektiiv- ja t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga on lubatud ette n&auml;ha t&auml;iendavad alused l&uuml;hendatud t&ouml;&ouml;aja rakendamiseks, kui sellega ei kaasne palgatingimuste halvenemine. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A collective agreement or employment contract may prescribe supplementary bases for application of reduced working time unless this results in a deterioration of wage conditions. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aja l&uuml;hendamise tingimused </eesti>
<inglise>Conditions for reducing working time </inglise>
<eesti>Allmaat&ouml;&ouml;l ja tervistkahjustaval t&ouml;&ouml;l t&ouml;&ouml;tajate t&ouml;&ouml;aega l&uuml;hendatakse, kui nad t&ouml;&ouml;tavad neis tingimustes v&auml;hemalt 75 protsenti k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 9 s&auml;testatud &uuml;ldisest t&ouml;&ouml;ajast. </eesti>
<inglise>The working time of employees engaged in underground work or work which poses a health hazard is reduced if they work under such conditions for at least 75 per cent of the general working time provided for in &sect; 9 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Igap&auml;evase t&ouml;&ouml;aja kestus </eesti>
<inglise>Duration of daily working time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riiklik t&ouml;&ouml;ajanorm viiep&auml;evase t&ouml;&ouml;n&auml;dalaga t&ouml;&ouml;tamisel on kaheksa tundi p&auml;evas 40-tunnise t&ouml;&ouml;n&auml;dala, seitse tundi p&auml;evas 35-tunnise t&ouml;&ouml;n&auml;dala, kuus tundi p&auml;evas 30-tunnise t&ouml;&ouml;n&auml;dala, viis tundi p&auml;evas 25-tunnise t&ouml;&ouml;n&auml;dala ja neli tundi p&auml;evas 20-tunnise t&ouml;&ouml;n&auml;dala puhul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For a five day working week, the national standard for working time is eight hours per day for a 40-hour working week, seven hours per day for a 35-hour working week, six hours per day for a 30-hour working week, five hours per day for a 25-hour working week and four hours per day for a 20-hour working week. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;ib summeeritud t&ouml;&ouml;aja arvestuse korral rakendada k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes ette n&auml;htud igap&auml;evase t&ouml;&ouml;aja kestusest erinevat t&ouml;&ouml;tundide arvu p&auml;evas (vahetuses), kusjuures see ei v&otilde;i &uuml;letada 12 tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon recording total working time, an employer may apply a number of working hours per day (shift) which is different from the duration of daily working time provided for in subsection (1) of this section (in shifts), but this shall not exceed twelve hours. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) 13-14-aastaste t&ouml;&ouml;tajate t&ouml;&ouml;aja kestus ei v&otilde;i &uuml;letada summeeritud t&ouml;&ouml;aja arvestuse korral viit tundi, 15-16-aastastel t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel kuut tundi ja 17-aastastel t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel seitset tundi p&auml;evas. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon the recording of total working time, the duration of working time of employees who are 13-14 years of age shall not exceed five hours per day, the duration of working time of employees who are 15-16 years of age shall not exceed six hours per day and the duration working time of employees who are 17 years of age shall not exceed seven hours per day. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&auml;isealistele t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele on lubatud rakendada erandina t&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori n&otilde;usolekul k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatust pikema t&ouml;&ouml;tundide arvuga vahetust. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) As an exception, shifts with a greater number of working hours than those provided for in subsection (2) of this section may be applied with respect to adult employees with the agreement of the labour inspector of the location (residence) of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; </eesti>
<inglise>Overtime </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;ks loetakse t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;tamist &uuml;le kokkulepitud t&ouml;&ouml;ajanormi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Overtime is work by employees which exceeds the agreed standard for working time. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; tegemine on lubatud poolte kokkuleppel, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 3. l&otilde;ikes loetletud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Overtime is permitted by agreement of the parties except in the cases specified in subsection (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;taja on kohustatud t&auml;itma t&ouml;&ouml;andja korralduse &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; tegemiseks j&auml;rgmistel erandjuhtudel: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Employees are required to comply with orders of employers to work overtime in the following exceptional cases: </inglise>
<eesti>1) loodus&otilde;nnetuse v&otilde;i tootmisavarii &auml;rahoidmiseks v&otilde;i nende tagaj&auml;rgede kiireks k&otilde;rvaldamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) for the prevention of a natural disaster or industrial accident or the expeditious elimination of the consequences thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &otilde;nnetusjuhtumi, t&ouml;&ouml;andja vara h&auml;vimise v&otilde;i riknemise &auml;rahoidmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) for the prevention of an accident, destruction of or damage to the property of the employer; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;protsessi l&otilde;puleviimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>3) for the completion of the work process. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Vahetust&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;le mitteilmumisel, kui t&ouml;&ouml;s ei v&otilde;i tekkida vaheaega, on t&ouml;&ouml;taja kohustatud teatama sellest t&ouml;&ouml;andajale ja j&auml;tkama t&ouml;&ouml;d kui &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;d. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a shift worker fails to come to work and the work cannot be discontinued, employees are required to notify the employer thereof and continue the work as overtime. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud pidama &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; arvestust iga t&ouml;&ouml;taja ja iga &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; juhu kohta eraldi. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Employers are required to keep a record of overtime for every employee and every case of overtime separately. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; piiramine </eesti>
<inglise>Restriction on overtime </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;le on keelatud rakendada: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following shall not be required to work overtime: </inglise>
<eesti>1) rasedat; </eesti>
<inglise>1) pregnant women; </inglise>
<eesti>2) alaealist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) minors; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;tajat, kellele &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; on keelatud arsti otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>3) employees who are not allowed to work overtime by the decision of a doctor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Naist, kes kasvatab lapsinvaliidi v&otilde;i alla 14-aastast last v&otilde;i isikut, kes hooldab I grupi invaliidi, v&otilde;ib rakendada &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;le k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 13 3. l&otilde;ikes loetletud juhtudel &uuml;ksnes tema n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A woman raising a disabled child or child under fourteen years of age or a person taking care of a Category I disabled person may only be required to work overtime in the cases specified in subsection 13 (3) of this Act with his or her consent. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; piirnormid </eesti>
<inglise>Standard limits on overtime </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; piirnorm &uuml;he t&ouml;&ouml;taja kohta on 200 tundi kalendriaastas. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The standard limit on overtime per employee is 200 hours per calendar year. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;tajat ei ole lubatud rakendada &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;le nelja tunni p&auml;evas. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employees shall not be required to work overtime for more than four hours per day. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahetuse kestus koos &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml;ga ei tohi &uuml;letada 12 tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>The duration of a shift including overtime shall not exceed twelve hours. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kehtestatud &uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; piirnorme ei rakendata k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 13 3. l&otilde;ike 1 punktis toodud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The established standard limits on overtime do not apply in the cases specified in clause 13 (3) 1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Valveaeg </eesti>
<inglise>On call time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;del, kus t&ouml;&ouml;taja peab olema t&ouml;&ouml;andjale kokkulepitud kohas k&auml;ttesaadav etten&auml;gematute, edasil&uuml;kkamatute t&ouml;&ouml;de tegemiseks oma puhkeajal v&otilde;i kehtivad puhkeaja kasutamise suhtes erin&otilde;uded, on lubatud kehtestada lisaks &uuml;ldisele t&ouml;&ouml;aja kestusele valveaeg. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In addition to the general duration of working time, on call time may be established for work where employees must be at the disposal of the employer in agreed locations for the performance of unforeseen and urgent tasks during their rest time, or if special requirements apply to the use of rest time. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Valveaja kestus ei v&otilde;i &uuml;letada 24 tundi kuus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The duration of on call time shall not exceed twenty-four hours per month. </inglise>
<eesti>Neid tunde ei arvata t&ouml;&ouml;aja hulka ning nende eest maksab t&ouml;&ouml;andja lisatasu. </eesti>
<inglise>Such hours are not included in working time and the employer shall pay additional remuneration therefor. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Valveaja kestus, rakendamise kord ja lisatasu suurus m&auml;&auml;ratakse kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The duration of and procedure for application of on call time, and the amount of additional remuneration shall be determined by a collective agreement or employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohakaaslaste t&ouml;&ouml;aeg </eesti>
<inglise>Working time of person with second job </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kohakaasluse alusel t&ouml;&ouml;tava isiku t&ouml;&ouml;aeg ei v&otilde;i &uuml;letada 20 tundi n&auml;dalas. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The working time of a person with a second job shall not exceed twenty hours per week at the second job. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui kohakaasluse alusel t&ouml;&ouml;tav isik t&ouml;&ouml;tab p&otilde;hit&ouml;&ouml;l osalise t&ouml;&ouml;ajaga, ei v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;aeg p&otilde;hit&ouml;&ouml;l ja kohakaasluse alusel kokku &uuml;letada 60 tundi n&auml;dalas. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a person with a second job works part-time at his or her principal job, the total working time in the principal job and the second job together shall not exceed sixty hours per week. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Osaline t&ouml;&ouml;aeg </eesti>
<inglise>Part-time working time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Osaline t&ouml;&ouml;aeg on t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures kehtestatud t&ouml;&ouml;aja normist l&uuml;hem t&ouml;&ouml;aeg, mida rakendatakse t&ouml;&ouml;taja ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja kokkuleppel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Part-time working time is working time which is shorter than the established standard for working time at the place of employment and which is applied by agreement of an employee and employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;mahu v&otilde;i tellimuste ajutisel v&auml;henemisel on t&ouml;&ouml;andjal &otilde;igus kehtestada osaline t&ouml;&ouml;aeg Eesti Vabariigi t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse &sect;-s 68 (RT 1992, 15/16, 241; 1993, 10, 150; I 1993, 26, 441; 1995, 14, 170; 16, 228; 1996, 3, 57; 40, 773; 45, 850; 49, 953; 1997, 5/6, 32) etten&auml;htud korras ja tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the event of a temporary decrease in work volume or orders, an employer has the right to establish part-time working time pursuant to the procedure and under the conditions prescribed in &sect; 68 of the Republic of Estonia Employment Contracts Act (RT 1992, 15/16, 241; 1993, 10, 150; I 1993, 26, 441; 1995, 14, 170; 16, 228; 1996, 3, 57; 40, 773; 45, 850; 49, 953; 1997, 5/6, 32). </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raseda ning naise soovil, kes kasvatab lapsinvaliidi v&otilde;i alla 14-aastast last, on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud rakendama talle osalist t&ouml;&ouml;aega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) At the request of a pregnant woman or a woman raising a disabled child or child under fourteen years of age, an employer is required to apply part-time working time with respect to such person. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tamine &otilde;htusel ja &ouml;&ouml;ajal </eesti>
<inglise>Work during evening or night time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;htuseks ajaks loetakse aega kella 18.00-22.00, &ouml;&ouml;ajaks aega kella 22.00 &otilde;htul kuni kella 6.00 hommikul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Evening time is the time between 18.00-22.00, and night time is the time from 22.00 until 6.00. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Ouml;&ouml;ajal on keelatud t&ouml;&ouml;le rakendada: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following shall not be required to work during night time: </inglise>
<eesti>1) rasedat; </eesti>
<inglise>1) pregnant women; </inglise>
<eesti>2) alaealist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) minors; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;tajat, kellele see on keelatud arsti otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>3) employees who are not allowed to work during night time by the decision of a doctor. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Naist, kes kasvatab lapsinvaliidi v&otilde;i alla 14-aastast last, v&otilde;i isikut, kes hooldab I grupi invaliidi, v&otilde;ib rakendada t&ouml;&ouml;le &ouml;&ouml;ajal &uuml;ksnes tema n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A woman raising a disabled child or child under fourteen years of age or a person taking care of a Category I disabled person may only be required to work during night time with his or her consent. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kollektiivlepinguga v&otilde;ib ette n&auml;ha t&auml;iendavaid piiranguid t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;lerakendamiseks &otilde;htusel ja &ouml;&ouml;ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Supplementary restrictions on requiring employees to work during evening or night time may be prescribed by a collective agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aja kestus &ouml;&ouml;ajal </eesti>
<inglise>Duration of working time during night time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;ldise t&ouml;&ouml;aja rakendamisel l&uuml;hendatakse vahetuse kestust &ouml;&ouml;ajal &uuml;he tunni v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon the application of general working time, the duration of a shift shall be reduced by one hour during night time. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vahetuse kestus &ouml;&ouml;ajal v&otilde;rdsustatakse p&auml;evasega, kui see on v&auml;ltimatu tootmistingimuste t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The duration of a shift during night time may be equal to that during the day if this is unavoidable due to production conditions. </inglise>
<eesti>III peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter III </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aja korraldus ja arvestamine </eesti>
<inglise>Organisation and Recording of Working Time </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;ajare iimi kehtestamine </eesti>
<inglise>Establishment of working time regime </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;ajare iimi, s.o. t&ouml;&ouml;aja alguse ja l&otilde;pu, puhkamiseks ja einetamiseks antava aja, samuti muud vaheajad t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva kestel, &uuml;hest vahetusest teise &uuml;lemineku aja ning korra m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjade, vahetuste ajakavaga v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The working time regime, i.e. the beginning and end of working time, time provided for rest and meals, other breaks during a working day, and the time and procedure for alternating shifts shall be determined by employers by internal work procedure rules, shift schedules or an employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;ajare&zcaron;iimi kehtestamisel elanikkonna teenindamise ettev&otilde;tetes, asutustes ja organisatsioonides peab t&ouml;&ouml;andja arvestama kohaliku omavalitsuse t&auml;itevorgani ettekirjutusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employers shall observe the precepts of local government executive bodies upon establishing the working time regimes of enterprises, agencies and organisations providing services to the public. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jaotamine osadeks </eesti>
<inglise>Division of working day into parts </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;del, kus see on vajalik t&ouml;&ouml; iseloomu t&otilde;ttu, v&otilde;ib kollektiivlepinguga v&otilde;i kokkuleppel t&ouml;&ouml;tajaga jagada t&ouml;&ouml;aja osadeks, kusjuures vaheaeg v&otilde;ib &uuml;letada k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis 24 puhkamiseks ja einetamiseks etten&auml;htud vaheaja kestust. </eesti>
<inglise>Working time may be divided into parts by a collective agreement or agreement with the employees where this is necessary due to the nature of the work, in which event breaks may exceed the duration of the breaks for rest and meals prescribed in &sect; 24 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aja arvestus </eesti>
<inglise>Recording of working time </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud pidama k&otilde;igi t&ouml;&ouml;tajate t&ouml;&ouml;aja arvestust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employers are required to keep a record of working time for all employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ettev&otilde;tetes, asutustes ja muudes organisatsioonides, kus t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste t&otilde;ttu pole v&otilde;imalik kinni pidada t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;n&auml;dala &uuml;ldisest normist, on lubatud kohaldada t&ouml;&ouml;aja summeeritud arvestust pikema ajavahemiku ulatuses (kuu, kolm kuud, pool aastat v&otilde;i muu ajavahemik). </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In enterprises, agencies and other organisations where it is not possible to adhere to the general standard for working day or working week due to working conditions, the recording of total working time for longer periods of time (a month, three months, a half year or other period of time) is permitted. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui arvestusperioodiks on kolmest kuust pikem ajavahemik, on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;aja summeeritud arvestuse tingimused koosk&otilde;lastama oma asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektoriga. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the recording period is a period of time longer than three months, an employer is required to co-ordinate the conditions for the recording of total working time with the labour inspector of the location (residence) of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;aja summeeritud arvestuse korral koostab t&ouml;&ouml;andja ajakava kogu arvestusperioodi kohta ja teeb selle teatavaks t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele v&auml;hemalt viis p&auml;eva enne arvestusperioodi algust. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon recording total working time, an employer shall prepare a schedule for the entire recording period and notify employees thereof at least five days before the beginning of the recording period. </inglise>
<eesti>IV peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter IV </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkeaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Rest Time </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaheaeg puhkamiseks ja einetamiseks </eesti>
<inglise>Breaks for rest and meals </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vaheaega puhkamiseks ja einetamiseks v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;tajale anda kestusega kuni kaks tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employees may be provided with up to two hours of breaks for rest and meals. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vaheaeg puhkamiseks ja einetamiseks antakse mitte hiljem kui p&auml;rast viis tundi kestnud t&ouml;&ouml;tamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A break for rest and meals shall be provided not later than after five hours of work. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;ib vaheaega kasutada oma &auml;ran&auml;gemise j&auml;rgi ja tal on &otilde;igus sel ajal ettev&otilde;tte, asutuse v&otilde;i muu organisatsiooni territooriumilt lahkuda, kui kollektiivlepingus v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus pole kokku lepitud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Employees may use breaks at their discretion and they have the right to leave the territory of the enterprise, agency or other organisation at that time unless otherwise agreed in a collective agreement or employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Puhkamiseks ja einetamiseks antava vaheaja algus ja l&otilde;pp m&auml;&auml;ratakse t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjade, vahetuste ajakava v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The beginning and end of breaks provided for rest and meals shall be determined by the internal work procedure rules, a shift schedule or employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;del, kus t&ouml;&ouml; iseloomu t&otilde;ttu pole v&otilde;imalik anda vaheaega puhkamiseks ja einetamiseks, luuakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale v&otilde;imalus einetada t&ouml;&ouml; ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In the case of work where, due to the nature of the work, it is not possible to provide breaks for rest and meals, employees shall be provided with an opportunity to eat during working time. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Vaheaega puhkamiseks ja einetamiseks ei arvata t&ouml;&ouml;aja hulka, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 5. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud einetamise aeg. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Breaks for rest and meals are not included in working time, except the time for meals prescribed in subsection (5) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaheajad lapse toitmiseks </eesti>
<inglise>Breaks for feeding child </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isikule, kes kasvatab alla poolteiseaastast last, antakse peale &uuml;ldise vaheaja puhkamiseks ja einetamiseks lisavaheajad lapse toitmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person raising a child under one and one half years of age shall be provided with additional breaks to feed the child in addition to the general breaks for rest and meals. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Need vaheajad antakse v&auml;hemalt iga kolme tunni j&auml;rel kestusega iga kord mitte alla 30 minuti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Such breaks shall be provided at least every three hours with a duration of not less than 30 minutes every time. </inglise>
<eesti>Kahe v&otilde;i enama kuni poolteiseaastase lapse toitmiseks antava vaheaja kestus peab olema v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks tund. </eesti>
<inglise>The duration of a break provided for feeding two or more children of up to one and one half years of age shall be at least one hour. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Isiku soovil liidetakse lapse toitmiseks etten&auml;htud vaheajad puhkamise ning einetamise vaheajaga v&otilde;i l&uuml;hendatakse t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva vastava ajavahemiku v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a person so requests, the breaks prescribed for feeding a child are added to the breaks for rest and meals, or the working day is reduced by the corresponding period of time. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Vaheajad lapse toitmiseks arvatakse t&ouml;&ouml;aja hulka ja nende eest s&auml;ilitatakse keskmine palk riigieelarve vahenditest riikliku sotsiaalkindlustuse eelarve kaudu Sotsiaalministeeriumi poolt kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Breaks for feeding a child are included in working time and payment of average wages shall be continued in respect of the breaks from state budget funds through the state social insurance budget pursuant to the procedure established by the Ministry of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>[ 16.01.1995 ] </eesti>
<inglise>[ 16.01.1995 ] </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Muud t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evasisesed vaheajad </eesti>
<inglise>Other breaks during working day </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Seaduse, haldusakti, kollektiivlepingu, t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjade, vahetuste ajakava v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga v&otilde;ib ette n&auml;ha lisaks k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvides 24 ja 25 kehtestatud vaheaegadele muid vaheaegu t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva v&otilde;i vahetuse jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In addition to the breaks established in &sect;&sect; 24 and 25 of this Act, other breaks may be prescribed during a working day or shift by law, administrative legislation, a collective agreement, internal work procedure rules, a shift schedule or employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud vaheajad arvatakse t&ouml;&ouml;aja hulka. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The breaks provided for in subsection (1) of this section are included in working time. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahetustevaheline puhkeaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Rest time between shifts </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vahetustevahelise puhkeaja kestus peab olema v&auml;hemalt 11 tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The duration of rest time between shifts shall be at least eleven hours. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Erandeid k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatust v&otilde;ib teha seaduse, haldusakti v&otilde;i kollektiivlepinguga t&ouml;&ouml;aja summeeritud arvestuse korral. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Exceptions to subsection (1) of this section may be made by law, administrative legislation or a collective agreement upon the recording of total working time. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkep&auml;evad </eesti>
<inglise>Days off </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tajal on v&auml;hemalt kaks puhkep&auml;eva n&auml;dalas. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employees shall have at least two days off per week. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ldised puhkep&auml;evad on laup&auml;ev ja p&uuml;hap&auml;ev. </eesti>
<inglise>Standard days off are Saturday and Sunday. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ettev&otilde;tetes, asutustes ja muudes organisatsioonides, kus t&ouml;&ouml; iseloomu t&otilde;ttu laup&auml;eval ja p&uuml;hap&auml;eval t&ouml;&ouml;tatakse, n&auml;hakse puhkep&auml;evad ette t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjade v&otilde;i vahetuste ajakavaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In enterprises, agencies and other organisations where, due to the nature of the work, work is done on Saturday and Sunday, days off shall be prescribed by internal work procedure rules or shift schedules. </inglise>
<eesti>Sellisel juhul antakse puhkep&auml;evad &uuml;ksteisele j&auml;rgnevatel n&auml;dalap&auml;evadel. </eesti>
<inglise>In such cases, days off shall be given on consecutive weekdays. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;aja summeeritud arvestuse korral peab igan&auml;dalase katkematu puhkeaja kestus olema v&auml;hemalt 36 tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon the recording of total working time, the duration of weekly uninterrupted rest time shall be at least thirty-six hours. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. ja 3. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatust on lubatud erandeid teha katkestamatu tootmisprotsessiga ettev&otilde;tetes ja muudes organisatsioonides nende asukoha t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Exceptions to subsections (2) and (3) of this section may be made in enterprises with uninterrupted production processes and other organisations with the consent of the labour inspector of their location. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Lapsinvaliidi vanema (eestkostja, hooldaja) t&auml;iendav tasuline puhkep&auml;ev </eesti>
<inglise>Additional day off with pay for parent (guardian, curator) of disabled child </inglise>
<eesti>Lapsinvaliidi &uuml;hel vanematest (eestkostjal, hooldajal) on &otilde;igus lisapuhkep&auml;evale kuus, mille eest tasutakse keskmise palga alusel riigieelarve vahenditest riikliku sotsiaalkindlustuse eelarve kaudu Sotsiaalministeeriumi poolt kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>One parent (guardian, curator) of a disabled child has the right to an additional day off per month, for which remuneration based on the average salary is paid from state budget funds through the state social insurance budget pursuant to the procedure established by the Ministry of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>[ 16.01.1995 ] </eesti>
<inglise>[ 16.01.1995 ] </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;lerakendamine puhkep&auml;eval </eesti>
<inglise>Requiring employees to work on days off </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;lerakendamine puhkep&auml;eval on lubatud tema n&otilde;usolekul, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employees may be required to work on days off with their consent, except in the cases prescribed in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;taja on kohustatud puhkep&auml;eval t&ouml;&ouml;le tulema j&auml;rgmistel juhtudel: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employees are required to come to work on days off in the following cases: </inglise>
<eesti>1) loodus&otilde;nnetuse v&otilde;i tootmisavarii &auml;rahoidmiseks v&otilde;i nende tagaj&auml;rgede kiireks k&otilde;rvaldamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) for the prevention of a natural disaster or industrial accident or for the expeditious elimination of the consequences thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &otilde;nnetusjuhtumi, t&ouml;&ouml;andja vara h&auml;vimise v&otilde;i riknemise &auml;rahoidmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>2) for the prevention of an accident, destruction of or damage to the property of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Puhkep&auml;eval on keelatud t&ouml;&ouml;le rakendada: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The following shall not be required to work on days off: </inglise>
<eesti>1) rasedat; </eesti>
<inglise>1) pregnant women; </inglise>
<eesti>2) alaealist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) minors; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;tajat, kellele see on keelatud arsti otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>3) employees who are not allowed to work on such days by the decision of a doctor. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Naist, kes kasvatab lapsinvaliidi v&otilde;i alla 14-aastast last, v&otilde;i isikut, kes hooldab I grupi invaliidi, v&otilde;ib puhkep&auml;eval t&ouml;&ouml;le rakendada k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud juhtudel &uuml;ksnes tema n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A woman raising a disabled child or child under fourteen years of age or a person taking care of a Category I disabled person may only be required to work on a day off in the cases prescribed in subsection (2) of this section with his or her consent. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>Doonoriks oleva t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;lt &auml;ra lubamine </eesti>
<inglise>Allowing employees who are blood donors to be absent from work </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud lubama doonoriks oleva t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;lt &auml;ra vere andmise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>Employers are required to allow employees who are blood donors to be absent from work on the day that blood is given. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigip&uuml;had </eesti>
<inglise>Public holidays </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tajate puhkeaja hulka kuuluvad riigip&uuml;had, mille loetelu s&auml;testatakse eraldi seadusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Public holidays the list of which is provided by a separate Act are included in the rest time of employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Uusaasta ja esimese j&otilde;ulup&uuml;ha eelsel t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval l&uuml;hendatakse t&ouml;&ouml;aja kestust kolme tunni v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The duration of working time is reduced by three hours on the working day preceding New Year's Day and Christmas Day. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;ib riigip&uuml;hadel t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;le rakendada, kui see on tingitud elanike teenindamise vajadusest, t&ouml;&ouml; iseloomust (katkematu tootmisprotsess) v&otilde;i tootmish&auml;davajadusest t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse paragrahv 65 2. l&otilde;ikes loetletud asjaoludel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Employers may require employees to work on public holidays if this results from the need to provide services to the public, the nature of the work (uninterruptable production process) or from urgent production requirements due to circumstances specified in subsection 65 (2) of the Employment Contracts Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkused </eesti>
<inglise>Holidays </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajate puhkused ja nende andmise kord on s&auml;testatud Eesti Vabariigi puhkuseseaduses (RT 1992, 37, 481; I 1993, 10, 150; 1994, 84, 1474; 1995, 16, 228). </eesti>
<inglise>The holidays of employees and the procedure for granting them are provided for in the Republic of Estonia Holiday Act (RT 1992, 37, 481; I 1993, 10, 150; 1994, 84, 1474; 1995, 16, 228). </inglise>
